                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;Thank You Jim for feedback.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have mixed feelings too. I certainly wouldn&#039;t want to hurt people&#039;s willingness to experiment or put them under similar pressure they experience in regular job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regardless of using checklist we are going to facilitate this event in same fashion as previous ones. We are going to introduce exercises for each session as usual so that it&#039;s possible to have reasonable retrospectives with whole group afterwards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Checklist would be just additional/optional thing. It certainly isn&#039;t going to contain all exercises which will happen during whole day. I would like to keep it as short as possible (&amp;lt;7 items) so that it doesn&#039;t confuse people or distract them from more important stuff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PS: Delete code contains 6 checkboxes (one for each session) and it would be introduced as mandatory as usual. It should therefore be pretty easy for most of the people to achieve this if they follow the rules. I like idea of having some items which one might achieve easily.&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
